Defendant Brandon D Spaeth in court with attorney Darryl E Smith.  Defendant Brandon D Spaeth in custody.  Lucy Kronforst appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court for continuation of Sentencing.  Hearing proceeded.  

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 1/2 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence being served with credit for 0 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 30 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 3 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program ONLY AFTER SERVING THE FIRST YEAR OF THIS SENTENCE.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Take any prescribed medication only in the manner as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program and/or Anger Management- agent to determine which program or if both are necessary;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;

The Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $600.00 plus all mandatory costs, penalties, and surcharges, including $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge- bail to apply. Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 3 years.  Court ordered defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 3 years.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Appeal rights given by the court.
